1. Oil-based paints take longer to dry than water-based paints.
2. Oil-based paints have strong fumes that can be hazardous to health.
3. Oil-based paints require solvents like mineral spirits or turpentine for clean-up, which can be hazardous to health and the environment.
4. Oil-based paints can be difficult to mix and blend.
5. Oil-based paints are more likely to stain surfaces and skin.
6. Oil-based paints require special clean-up procedures and equipment.
7. Oil-based paints can be messy and difficult to clean up with rags or paper towels.
8. Oil-based paints can take days or weeks to fully harden and cure.